      "type": "Claim",
      "name": "FEA credibility claim: non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending",
      "description": "The FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes implementations) produces predictions of construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending that fall within pre-specified acceptance bounds (<10% relative QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96) across N=11 experimental specimens tested at two independent laboratories. This claim supports regulatory submission as evidence that the computational model is sufficiently credible for the stated context of use at Medium model risk level.",
      "purpose": "Support 510(k) submission by demonstrating that FEA predictions are credible surrogates for bench testing of non-cannulated pedicle screw constructs under F1717 compression-bending loading.",
